                                <p>
                                    Dear Delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>In my capacity as the President for the European Council (EC), it is an honour to welcome you to DSMUN 2016. I am currently in my final school year as a student in the ISC Humanities stream. My range of interests encompasses debating, MUN-ing, dramatics and squash. I have been an avid MUN-ner since the 9th grade and have attended 7 MUN conferences over the past few years, including the prestigious Harvard MUN in India. Diplomacy and foreign relations are areas of study that immensely interest me, making MUN-ing natural extension of my interests.</p>
                                <p>The first agenda is a seemingly more pertinent issue that deals with the current refugee influx into the European Union. This debate will be different from the ones in other similar committees you might have visited earlier because the mandate of the European Council on this issue is much broader than any other committee’s The second Agenda will require immense reading and understanding of the structural set up of the EU, as it deals with an area of EU policy that needs to be discussed taking into account the recent issue of ‘Brexit’ as an epitomic example of the agenda’s implications.</p>
                                <p>I would like to hand you a few basic tips to make sure our discussion takes place in a structured and coherent fashion and that we arrive at the best possible outcome.  First off, do try and structure the debate in an orderly manner; this applies to the entire cabinet as well as individual speeches. Always remember that good in-depth research will be your best and only friend in this committee, when backed with substantivizes and practicality in your points. Thirdly, never shy away from critically analyzing the material that you gather. Lastly, do read about the mandate of this committee so you understand the powers that you, as delegates of your country, hold.</p>

                                <p>To conclude, I would like you to know that you are always welcome to address any doubts, clarifications or queries you may require to be answered through the course of your preparation to us, and expect prompt answers.</p>
                                <p>Embrace yourselves for three days of enriching debate, diplomacy and forging relationships that shall last with you forever. I look forward to seeing you here at Chandbagh,</p>
                                <div class="signing-off">
